Richie Benaud has died aged 84 in a Sydney hospice after battling skin cancer  . 
  The cricket commentator died peacefully in his sleep overnight surrounded by his wife Daphne and family . 
  Benaud had been receiving radiation treatment for skin cancer since November . 
  He was a veteran of 63 Test matches and one of Australia's most influential cricketers . 
  Cricket Australia has described him as a national treasure . 
  He played a pivotal role in the formation of World Series Cricket in the 1970s . 
  He anchored the Nine Network's cricket coverage in Australia for decades . 
 